==English==
[[Image:Lion waiting in Nambia.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A lion.]]

===Etymology===
From French ''[[#French|lion]]'', from Latin ''[[leo]]'', ''[[leonis]]''.

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/lī'ən/}}, {{IPA|/ˈlaɪən/}}, {{SAMPA|/"laI@n/}}
*{{audio|en-us-lion.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:[[Rhymes:English:-aɪən|Rhymes: -aɪən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A large [[cat]], ''Panthera leo'', native to Africa and formerly to much of Europe.  The term may apply to the species as a whole, to individuals, or to male individuals.  It also applies to related species like [[mountain lion]]s.

====Derived terms====
*[[cave lion]]
*[[lioness]]
*[[lionfish]]
*[[mountain lion]]

